And finally, we produce mobile apps

124
0:05:33.26,000 --> 0:05:36,000
that include narrated virtual tools.

125
0:05:37.26,000 --> 0:05:4,000
The more I got involved

126
0:05:40.26,000 --> 0:05:42,000
in the heritage field,

127
0:05:42.26,000 --> 0:05:45,000
the more it became clear to me

128
0:05:45.26,000 --> 0:05:48,000
that we are losing the sites

129
0:05:48.26,000 --> 0:05:51,000
and the stories faster than we can

130
0:05:51.26,000 --> 0:05:54,000
physically preserve them.

131
0:05:54.26,000 --> 0:05:56,000
Of course, earthquakes

132
0:05:56.26,000 --> 0:05:58,000
and all the natural phenomena --

133
0:05:58.26,000 --> 0:06:,000
floods, tornadoes, etc. --

134
0:06:00.26,000 --> 0:06:03,000
take their toll.

135
0:06:03.26,000 --> 0:06:06,000
However, what occurred to me was

136
0:06:06.26,000 --> 0:06:08,000
human-caused destruction, which was

137
0:06:08.26,000 --> 0:06:1,000
not only causing a significant portion

138
0:06:10.26,000 --> 0:06:13,000
of the destruction, but actually

139
0:06:13.26,000 --> 0:06:16,000
it was accelerating.

140
0:06:16.26,000 --> 0:06:18,000
This includes arson,

141
0:06:18.26,000 --> 0:06:2,000
urban sprawl,

142
0:06:20.26,000 --> 0:06:23,000
acid rain, not to mention

143
0:06:23.26,000 --> 0:06:25,000
terrorism and wars.

144
0:06:25.26,000 --> 0:06:28,000
It was getting more and more apparent

145
0:06:28.26,000 --> 0:06:3,000
that we're fighting a losing battle.

146
0:06:30.26,000 --> 0:06:32,000
We're losing our sites

147
0:06:32.26,000 --> 0:06:34,000
and the stories,

148
0:06:34.26,000 --> 0:06:36,000
and basically we're losing

149
0:06:36.26,000 --> 0:06:38,000
a piece -- and a significant piece --

150
0:06:38.26,000 --> 0:06:41,000
of our collective memory.

151
0:06:41.26,000 --> 0:06:43,000
Imagine us as a human race

152
0:06:43.26,000 --> 0:06:47,000
not knowing where we came from.

153
0:06:47.26,000 --> 0:06:5,000
Luckily, in the last two or three decades,

154
0:06:50.26,000 --> 0:06:53,000
digital technologies have been developing

155
0:06:53.26,000 --> 0:06:55,000
that have helped us to develop tools

156
0:06:55.26,000 --> 0:06:57,000
that we've brought to bear

157
0:06:57.26,000 --> 0:06:59,000
in the digital preservation,

158
0:06:59.26,000 --> 0:07:01,000
in our digital preservation war.

159
0:07:01.26,000 --> 0:07:03,000
This includes, for example,

160
0:07:03.26,000 --> 0:07:07,000
the 3D laser scanning systems,

161
0:07:07.26,000 --> 0:07:1,000
ever more powerful personal computers,

162
0:07:10.26,000 --> 0:07:12,000
3D graphics,

163
0:07:12.26,000 --> 0:07:15,000
high-definition digital photography,

164
0:07:15.26,000 --> 0:07:18,000
not to mention the Internet.

165
0:07:18.26,000 --> 0:07:2,000
Because of this accelerated

166
0:07:20.26,000 --> 0:07:22,000
pace of destruction,

167
0:07:22.26,000 --> 0:07:24,000
it became clear to us that we needed

168
0:07:24.26,000 --> 0:07:27,000
to challenge ourselves and our partners

169
0:07:27.26,000 --> 0:07:29,000
to accelerate our work.

170
0:07:29.26,000 --> 0:07:31,000
And we created a project

171
0:07:31.26,000 --> 0:07:34,000
we call the CyArk 500 Challenge --

172
0:07:34.26,000 --> 0:07:37,000
and that is to digitally preserve

173
0:07:37.26,000 --> 0:07:4,000
500 World Heritage Sites

174
0:07:40.26,000 --> 0:07:42,000
in five years.

175
0:07:42.26,000 --> 0:07:44,000
We do have the technology

176
0:07:44.26,000 --> 0:07:46,000
that's scaleable,

177
0:07:46.26,000 --> 0:07:5,000
and our network of global partners

178
0:07:50.26,000 --> 0:07:53,000
has been expanding and can be expanded

179
0:07:53.26,000 --> 0:07:55,000
at a rapid rate,

180
0:07:55.26,000 --> 0:07:57,000
so we're comfortable

181
0:07:57.26,000 --> 0:08:,000
that this task can be accomplished.

182
0:08:00.26,000 --> 0:08:03,000
However, to me, the 500 is

183
0:08:03.26,000 --> 0:08:07,000
really just the first 500.

